    {
      "id": "f47f0dacd469a5c89db183eb68743f0c6cb2313d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 12,
        "name": "wangdi",
        "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
        "username": "wangdi",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-03-18 07:11:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAlex, since we will add get_info to get change log index (from MDT to MDD) anyway,  so why can not just remove root_get, and replace it with get_info (KEY_ROOT). If you insist, I can change that, but I thought adding individual API for each INFO get might be not good? though I might miss sth.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "37b4652d9a1e5b09244705df058eba9dfdee82f5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-18 07:17:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nget_info() (or ioctl) is a bad thing in general.. especially when it duplicates existing good methods. and even more especially if it brings no value after all (see that \"historic\" path functionality is not implemented).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "d36f0d6cb99dcd126c37e2070a0713384b57375c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-03-18 09:02:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nBuild Started http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/14105/ ",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "a88a500460acd9dfa2aba06cf9b9627d8ff86da2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-18 09:14:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nActually, I'd be happy if MDS_GETSTATUS ->mdo_root_get() was replaced by mdo_lookup(\"ROOT\").  This would be a step in the direction to allow clients to mount sub-trees of the filesystem.\n\nBefore we opened that up to actual requests from the user, we'd need to filter or otherwise mark datasets as being exported to users, so that mdo_lookup(\"CONFIGS\") or something similar was blocked, but it would at least remove the root_get() method and replace it with a common method.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "2c674682679d69005b30d78a064603c6293e060b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-18 09:19:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI'm fine with that",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "1f1a3a19db3e27b5913c39d21d45bfc47ff8ac2e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
